    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/06-rl-infra/04-verl.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Two failure modes: pure single-controller funnels all batch data through one driver (bottleneck) and can't express intra-stage collectives; pure multi-controller SPMD is fast but buries the RL control flow in replicated distributed code that's painful to change.; HybridFlow's resolution: single-controller BETWEEN stages (one readable driver loop over small logical batches) + multi-controller SPMD WITHIN each stage (heavy collectives stay inside a WorkerGroup, never touch the driver).; The dispatch decorator turns ONE driver call into N: DP_COMPUTE_PROTO shards the batch across data-parallel ranks but REPLICATES it within tensor-parallel ranks, runs the SPMD method on all ranks, then collects one representative per DP group and concatenates.; The 3D-HybridEngine reshards the actor's weights from the training layout (TP=p, FSDP/Megatron) to the rollout layout (TP=q, vLLM) by gathering within a small TP group then re-splitting p->q, all in GPU memory; only bf16 params move, optimizer state and gradients never leave the training layout.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  verl-dispatch-fanout, verl-reshard-p-to-q\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
